"            <h3 class=\"SECT3\"><a id=\"AEN50\" name=\"AEN50\">2.1.1\n"
"            Processor/Motherboard Support</a></h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:199
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>FreeBSD now has rudimentary support for\n"
"            HyperThreading (HTT). SMP kernels with the <tt\n"
"            class=\"LITERAL\">HTT</tt> kernel option will detect and\n"
"            start up the logical processors on HTT-capable\n"
"            machines. The logical processors will be treated like\n"
"            additional physical processors for the purposes of\n"
"            process scheduling.</p>\n"
"          </div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <h3 class=\"SECT3\"><a id=\"AEN60\" name=\"AEN60\">2.1.2 Boot\n"
"            Loaders</a></h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The PC98 bootloader now has support for booting from\n"
"            SCSI MO media.</p>\n"
"          </div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <h3 class=\"SECT3\"><a id=\"AEN63\" name=\"AEN63\">2.1.3\n"
"            Network Interface Support</a></h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "            <p>The cm driver now supports IPX.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=nge&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">nge</span>(4)</span></a> driver\n"
"            now supports network device <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=polling&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">polling</span>(4)</span></a>.</p>\n"
"          </div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:233
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <h3 class=\"SECT3\"><a id=\"AEN73\" name=\"AEN73\">2.1.4\n"
"            Network Protocols</a></h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>A <tt class=\"LITERAL\">FAST_IPSEC</tt> kernel option\n"
"            now allows the IPsec implementation to use the kernel\n"
"            <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=crypto&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">crypto</span>(4)</span></a>\n"
"            framework, along with its support for hardware\n"
"            cryptographic acceleration. More information can be\n"
"            found in the <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=fast_ipsec&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">fast_ipsec</span>(4)</span></a>\n"
"            manual page.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:256
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <div class=\"NOTE\">\n"
"              <blockquote class=\"NOTE\">\n"
"                <p><b>Note:</b> The <tt\n"
"                class=\"LITERAL\">FAST_IPSEC</tt> and <tt\n"
"                class=\"LITERAL\">IPSEC</tt> options are mutually\n"
"                exclusive.</p>\n"
"              </blockquote>\n"
"            </div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:267
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <div class=\"NOTE\">\n"
"              <blockquote class=\"NOTE\">\n"
"                <p><b>Note:</b> The <tt\n"
"                class=\"LITERAL\">FAST_IPSEC</tt> option is, at the\n"
"                moment, not compatible with IPv6 or the <tt\n"
"                class=\"LITERAL\">INET6</tt> option.</p>\n"
"              </blockquote>\n"
"            </div>\n"
"            <br />\n"
"            <br />\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:275
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>A <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=gre&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">gre</span>(4)</span></a> driver,\n"
"            which can encapsulate IP packets using GRE (RFC 1701)\n"
"            or minimal IP encapsulation for Mobile IP (RFC 2004),\n"
"            has been added.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:279
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>A bug in TCP NewReno, which caused premature exit\n"
"            from fast recovery with NewReno enabled, has been\n"
"            fixed.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The IP fragment reassembly code behaves more\n"
"            gracefully when receiving a large number of packet\n"
"            fragments (it is designed to be more resistant to\n"
"            fragment-based denial of service attacks).</p>\n"
"          </div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:291
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <h3 class=\"SECT3\"><a id=\"AEN97\" name=\"AEN97\">2.1.5\n"
"            Disks and Storage</a></h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:316
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=ata&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">ata</span>(4)</span></a> driver\n"
"            now supports accessing ATA devices as SCSI devices via\n"
"            the CAM layer and drivers (<a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=cd&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">cd</span>(4)</span></a>, <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=da&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">da</span>(4)</span></a>, <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=st&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">st</span>(4)</span></a>, and <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=pass&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">pass</span>(4)</span></a>). This\n"
"            feature requires <tt class=\"LITERAL\">device\n"
"            atapicam</tt> in the kernel configuration. More\n"
"            information can be found in <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=atapicam&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">atapicam</span>(4)</span></a>.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:326
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=matcd&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">matcd</span>(4)</span></a> driver\n"
"            has been removed due to concerns over its licensing\n"
"            terms. These issues are being addressed and this driver\n"
"            may reappear in a future release of FreeBSD. (This\n"
"            removal actually occurred in 4.7-RELEASE, but was not\n"
"            mentioned in the release notes.)</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The <a\n"
"            "
"href=\"http://www.FreeBSD.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=targ&sektion=4&manpath=FreeBSD+4.8-RELEASE\">\n"
"            <span class=\"CITEREFENTRY\"><span\n"
"            class=\"REFENTRYTITLE\">targ</span>(4)</span></a> driver\n"
"            has been rewritten and a new usermode has been added to\n"
"            <tt\n"
"            class=\"FILENAME\">/usr/share/examples/scsi_target</tt>\n"
"            that emulates a direct access device.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block + 4
#: content/en/releases/4.8R/relnotes-i386.adoc:339
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <p>The trm driver has been added to support SCSI\n"
"            adapters using the Tekram TRM-S1040 SCSI chipset.</p>\n"
"          </div>\n"
msgstr ""

